<em><br></em>
<p></p>
<p><span>These instructions take advantage of the&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"ht=
tps://getcomposer.org/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Composer</=
a><span>&nbsp;powered update systems in 5.3 for maintenance updates, so&nbs=
p;</span><span>make sure:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span>Familiarize yourself with the&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"confluen=
ce-link">&nbsp;</span><a href=3D"/display/EZP/Using+Composer">Using Compose=
r</a><span>&nbsp;page.</span></li>
<li><span>Update Composer, as found on&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://getcomposer.=
org/doc/03-cli.md#self-update" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Com=
poser self-update documentation</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p><em>For Upgrading from versions prior to 5.3 look at the&nbsp;<a href=3D=
"/display/EZP/Installation+and+Upgrade+Guides">Installation and Upgrade Gui=
des</a>.</em></p>
<h1 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-BeforeUpdating">Before&nbsp;Updating</=
h1>
<p>Follow <u>all*</u> instructions below that applies to the version you're=
&nbsp;updating&nbsp;from: when updating from 5.3.0 everything applies.</p>
<p><em>* The version you update to will always be the latests, hence the im=
portance of following all steps.</em></p>
<h2 class=3D"element" id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-From5.3.8andlower">F=
rom 5.3.8 and lower</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-UpdateComposerpluginsforComposerv1.1">=
Update&nbsp;Composer plugins for Composer v1.1</h3>
<p>Newer versions of Composer sometimes updates it's API's and as such we n=
eed to make sure our composer plugins up-to-date, so to&nbsp;:<span style=
=3D"color: rgb(0,98,147);">&nbsp;</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;"># First install Composer v1.0 that works with old version of ezpub=
lish-legacy-installer
php -r "copy('https://getcomposer.org/download/1.0.3/composer.phar', 'compo=
ser.phar');"

# As authentication is built in to composer now, we can remove the followin=
g plugin
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar remove --no-update --no-plugins bite=
xpert/composer-authstore-plugin


# Then install newer version of exponential-legacy-installer that works on Co=
mposer 1.1 (will warn about the outdated versions you have from before)
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar update --no-dev --prefer-dist --no-s=
cripts ezsystems/exponential-legacy-installer

# Then make sure composer is updated to latests
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar selfupdate&nbsp;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-From5.3.2andlower">From 5.3.2 and lowe=
r</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-RemoveZetaComponentspackagescausingcom=
poserconflicts">Remove Zeta Components packages causing composer conflicts<=
/h3>
<p>Issues with Zeta Components and Composer have been fixed <em>(new releas=
es of Zeta Components have been made to fix this)</em> so you should edit&n=
bsp;<code>composer.json</code>&nbsp;and remove any "<code>zetacomponents</c=
ode>" package like shown below:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar remove --no-update zetacomp=
onents/archive zetacomponents/authentication zetacomponents/authentication-=
database-tiein zetacomponents/base zetacomponents/cache zetacomponents/conf=
iguration zetacomponents/console-tools zetacomponents/database zetacomponen=
ts/debug zetacomponents/event-log zetacomponents/feed zetacomponents/image-=
conversion zetacomponents/mail zetacomponents/mvc-tools zetacomponents/mvc-=
authentication-tiein zetacomponents/persistent-object zetacomponents/php-ge=
nerator zetacomponents/signal-slot zetacomponents/system-information</pre>=
=20
</div>
</div>
<p>After doing this, verify that content of <code>composer.json</code> does=
 not contain any entries for <code>zetacomponents/</code> unless you have y=
our own dependencies on them. <code>exponential-kernel</code> and <code>ezpub=
lish-legacy</code> now always requires the specific versions of the Zeta Co=
mponents we use internally.</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-UpdateyourNginxconfiguration">Update y=
our Nginx configuration</h3>
<p>If you're using Nginx as your webserver instead of Apache, then make sur=
e to update&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/EZP/Nginx" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">Nginx vhost configuration</a>, changes since 5.3.0:&nbsp;<a href=3D"=
https://github.com/ezsystems/exponential-community/commit/d157a4ecb3ddf7a3825=
19fbb43ce311335cd8185" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">5.3.1</a>,&=
nbsp;<a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/exponential-community/commit/db5=
e0d4af62112e423cac6930f0549364438f756" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofol=
low">5.3.3&nbsp;</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-From5.3.3andlower">From 5.3.3 and lowe=
r</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Optional:Changecomposer.jsontoavoidocc=
asionalfatalerroronassetdumpwhenperformingcomposerupdate">Optional: Change =
composer.json to avoid occasional fatal error on asset dump when performing=
 composer update</h3>
<p>For issue&nbsp; <span class=3D"jira-issue resolved"> <a href=3D"https://=
jira.ez.no/browse/EZP-23492?src=3Dconfmacro" class=3D"jira-issue-key"><img =
class=3D"icon" src=3D"https://jira.ez.no/images/icons/issuetypes/improvemen=
t.png">EZP-23492</a> - <span class=3D"summary">Improve use of assetic dump =
with composer</span>=20
<!-- The new status lozengens support for JIRA 6.2 or later. Otherwise we u=
se the icon.--> <span class=3D"aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-s=
uccess jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">Closed</span> </span> &nbsp;comp=
oser.json should be edited to take full advantage of the improvement, see t=
he <a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/exponential-community/commit/ca781=
83990c12d3f2f32c3e59f0b253a09e1f8dd" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">following commit</a> for patch.</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-From5.3.4andlower">From 5.3.4 and lowe=
r</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Removeminkpackagecausingcomposerconfli=
ct">Remove mink package causing composer conflict</h3>
<p>Perform the following command to make sure you you are not affected by c=
onflicts caused by this package:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar remove --no-update --dev be=
hat/mink-selenium-driver </pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Recommended:Enablephp-opensslextension=
">Recommended: Enable php-openssl extension</h3>
<div class=3D"element">
This release fixes a vulnerability in the Exponential password recovery func=
tion. You need to have the PHP OpenSSL extension (ext-openssl) installed to=
 take full advantage of the improved security, but even without it security=
 is improved. See&nbsp;
<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/community-project/security-advisories/ezsa-20=
15-001-potential-vulnerability-in-exponential-password-recovery" style=3D"li=
ne-height: 1.4285715;" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Security Ad=
visory</a> for further information.
</div>
<h2 class=3D"element" id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-From5.3.8andlower.1"=
>From 5.3.8 and lower</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Updatesensiodistributionbundle">Update=
 sensio distribution bundle</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar require --no-plugins --no-up=
date "sensio/distribution-bundle ~2.3|~3.0"</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Updatingpackageswithcomposer">Updating=
 packages with composer</h1>
<p>With this command you'll only update all packages that have received upd=
ates:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;"># First delete the Symfony container cache to avoid error, on Wind=
ows use something like: DEL /F /Q /S exponential/cache/*/*ProjectContainer.ph=
p
rm exponential/cache/*/*ProjectContainer.php

# Now update all packages (will warn about outdated bitexpert/composer-auth=
store-plugin package first time you do this before that plugn is removed)
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 composer.phar update --no-dev --prefer-dist</pre>=
=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<p class=3D"title">Tip: Legacy extension autoload</p>
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Legacy extensions autoload must be regenerated when new classes are adde=
d. To make sure to avoid any issues always run this command after composer =
update:</p>
<p><code>php exponential/console exponential:legacy:script bin/php/ezpgeneratea=
utoloads.php --extension</code></p>
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-AfterUpdating"><span>After Updating</s=
pan></h1>
<p><span>Follow all instructions below that applies to the version&nbsp;you=
've updated from, i.e. if you are updating from 5.3.0 everything applies.</=
span></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Updatingfrom5.3.2andlower">Updating fr=
om 5.3.2 and lower</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Updatethedatabase">Update the database=
</h3>
<p>Import to your database the changes provided in:</p>
<pre class=3D"wordwrap"><span class=3D"line">/&lt;ezp5-root&gt;/exponential_l=
egacy/update/database/&lt;mysql|postgresql&gt;/5.3/dbupdate-5.3.2-to-5.3.3.=
sql</span></pre>
<p>And if you use Cluster (DFS) the following:</p>
<pre class=3D"wordwrap">/&lt;ezp5-root&gt;/exponential_legacy/update/database=
/mysql/5.3/dbupdate-cluster-5.3.2-to-5.3.3.sql</pre>
<h2 id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-Updatingfrom5.3.4andlower">Updating fr=
om 5.3.4 and lower</h2>
<h3 class=3D"wordwrap" id=3D"id-5.3.xUpdateInstructions-UpdateSolrconfigura=
tionandreindexcontent">Update Solr configuration and reindex content</h3>
<p>An eZ Find user needs to update their solr schema.xml.</p>
<p>For each solr core (located in ezfind/java/solr), you need to edit &lt;m=
y-core-name&gt;/conf/schema.xml</p>
<p>Around line 566, right after:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: xml; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;field name=3D"meta_priority_si" type=3D"sint" indexed=3D"true" =
stored=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Add the following lines:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: xml; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;!-- denormalised fields for hidden and visible path elements --=
&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_visible_path_si" type=3D"sint" indexed=3D"true" stor=
ed=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt;     &lt;!-- Visible Location path IDs=
 --&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_visible_path_string_ms" type=3D"mstring" indexed=3D"=
true" stored=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt; &lt;!-- Visible Location pa=
th string --&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_hidden_path_si" type=3D"sint" indexed=3D"true" store=
d=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt;     &lt;!-- Hidden Location path IDs -=
-&gt;
&lt;field name=3D"meta_hidden_path_string_ms" type=3D"mstring" indexed=3D"t=
rue" stored=3D"true" multiValued=3D"true"/&gt; &lt;!-- Hidden Location path=
 string --&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Now restart Solr, and re-index your content to be able to take advan=
tage of this&nbsp;improvement.</em></p>
    </div>
</body>
